articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: South Korean authorities investigating impeached President Yoon Seok Yeol were at his official residence on Wednesday to execute an arrest warrant over insurrection accusations related to his Dec. 3 martial law declaration.
articles.title: South Korea authorities at President Yoon's residence to execute arrest warrant

articles.author: Andrew Mills, Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Maayan Lubell
articles.description: Negotiators were near to hammering out the final details of a ceasefire in Gaza on Wednesday after marathon talks in Qatar, and the U.S. and Egyptian leaders promised to stay in close contact about a deal over the coming hours.
articles.title: Gaza ceasefire appears close as US, Egyptian leaders put focus on 'coming hours'

articles.author: Jeff Mason, Andrea Shalal
articles.description: President Joe Biden will cap his half-century political career with a final Oval Office speech, hoping to cement a legacy that has been overshadowed by Democrats' failure to stop Donald Trump from returning to the White House.
articles.title: Biden bids farewell from Oval Office as Trump looms over his legacy

articles.author: Jack Kim
articles.description: Yoon has been dogged by personal scandals, an unyielding opposition and rifts within his own party.
articles.title: South Korea's Yoon: Embittered survivor becomes first sitting president arrested

articles.author: Antoni Slodkowski, James Pomfret
articles.description: For years, the U.S. government has urged China to show "restraint" in pushing its claim on Taiwan and to drop military threats to bring the democratically governed island under its control.
articles.title: Trump's Greenland bid stirs debate in China about what to do with Taiwan

articles.author: Alan Charlish
articles.description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy will visit Warsaw on Wednesday, the Polish prime minister's office said, following what Poland has called a breakthrough in a historical dispute on wartime exhumations that has stood between the allies.
articles.title: Ukraine's Zelenskiy visits Poland after progress in World War Two dispute

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Bangladesh’s Supreme Court acquitted former Prime Minister Khaleda Zia in a 2008 corruption case on Wednesday, clearing the way for the ailing leader to fight parliamentary elections in the troubled South Asian country.
articles.title: Bangladesh's top court acquits former PM Khaleda in graft case

articles.author: Chad Terhune, Jorge Garcia
articles.description: Los Angeles firefighters on Tuesday braced for the return of dry, intense winds that could recharge two monstrous wildfires that have already killed at least 24 people, leveled entire neighborhoods and scorched an area the size of Washington, D.C.
articles.title: LA fires: Santa Ana hurricane-force winds could intensify wildfires

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Italy summoned Venezuela's chief diplomat in Rome on Wednesday to protest over a lack of information on the fate of an Italian national arrested in the Latin American country two months ago, the foreign ministry said.
articles.title: Italy protests to Venezuela over arrest of NGO worker

articles.author: Dominique Vidalon
articles.description: The prospects of French Prime Minister Francois Bayrou's minority government surviving in the long term appeared slimmer after the Socialist Party raised the threat of backing a no-confidence vote on Thursday.
articles.title: France's PM Bayrou weakened by Socialists' threat to back no-confidence vote
